Author: McDOWALL
Vol / Page: 14
Edition:
Quote: The fifth species is the rarest of all. It is the shortjawed kokopu (<i>Galaxias postvectis</i>), a species that is also rare as an adult. <i>Ibid.</i> 50 Shortjawed kokopu behave similarly to banded kokopu. They also climb falls and move well inland... Most shortjawed kokopu are found in small streams in unmodified native forest, usually in pools with thick cover,especially where there are piles of logs or boulders among which the fish can hide.
